{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1137a","heading":"Local law enforcement security training","label":"1137a Local law enforcement security training","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/ch4/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2022, and not as part of the National Transit Systems Security Act of 2007 which comprises this subchapter."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary of Homeland Security, in consultation with public and private sector stakeholders, may in a manner consistent with the protection of privacy rights, civil rights, and civil liberties, develop, through the Federal Law Enforcement Training Centers, a training program to enhance the protection, preparedness, and response capabilities of law enforcement agencies with respect to threats of terrorism and other threats, including targeted violence, at a surface transportation asset.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Requirements","label":"b Requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be informed by current information regarding tactics used by terrorists and others engaging in targeted violence;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"include tactical instruction tailored to the diverse nature of the surface transportation asset operational environment; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"prioritize training officers from law enforcement agencies that are eligible for or receive grants under sections 2003 or 2004 of the Homeland Security Act of 2002 ( and 605) and officers employed by railroad carriers that operate passenger service, including interstate passenger service.116 U.S.C. 6041So in original.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Report","label":"c Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the curriculum for the training and any changes to such curriculum;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an identification of any contracts entered into for the development or provision of training under the program;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"information on the law enforcement agencies the personnel of which received the training, and for each such agency, the number of participants; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the measures used to ensure the program was carried out to provide for protections of privacy rights, civil rights, and civil liberties.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Definitions","label":"d Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s1137a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs1137a%2Fd","sourc